- Small aliens will always be asleep when you find them, or will run away despite having bigger guns than you (halo)<br>
- Shooting an X-wing so your laser goes between its wings will still result in damaging it, even if you've already destroyed its shields (x-wing vs TIE)<br>
- The only hero in a huge strength-boosting suit of armour is the only hero who can only carry 2 guns at once, rather than the mandatory 500 (Halo again)<br>
- I can kill people 10 times my size by picking flowers then throwing bouncy balls at them, or by jumping on their head.<br>
- Touching a star makes you invincible, rather than flash-frying you.<br>
- Smarmy gits with a hex editor will always beat you, no matter how good you are<br>
- R-41 Starchasers (very slow) can get a missile lock on a TIE Advanced, despite the fact that it's moving at 100 kilometres a second, and has the decoy field on.<br>
-Balancing on the edge of a cliff with just your toes on the cliff and the rest of you over the edge will stop you from falling to your doom.<br>
- No matter how big the gun, it has to be held directly under your chin. Guns the size of people either shrink when held under your chin, or you bend double with it between your legs so you can only see the first couple of inches of the barrel. <p>'It's better to light a candle than curse the darkness, and better than both to remain unseen.'- NeoAngel. .................

