2. you can pump round after round of ammo from the most powerful weapon at an unarmed enemy, and he'll still kill you with his fists. ( Perfect FistSim from Perfect Dark)<br>
<br>
3. A society capable of building airships and hyper-advanced space vessels still relies on swords and staves as their main form of weaponry. <br>
<br>
4. A little pink blob with a large wooden mallet can kick the @#%$ out of anyone any day of the week.<br>
<br>
5. You can shoot your ally in the head with a rocket proppelled grenade, and he'll walk through the smoke unscathed. <br>
<br>
6. Rocket jumps ARE possible.<br>
<br>
7. If a guy has a really big automatic weapon pointed at your head, you don't have to do what he says, just slap the gun out of his hand and shoot him with it. <br>
<br>
8. A guy can destroy cities and kill waves of guards, even when hes been cleaved in half, and sealed, upside-down, in a gigantic crystal, hanging from the roof of a cave found in a crater in far off mountains.<br>
<br>
9. A pharmaceutical company also manufactures weapons of mass destruction in their basement.<br>
<br>
10. It's all right, you can trust a guy with big, spikey blonde hair, freaky armor, a gigantic sword, and an obvious mental instability to save your world, he's got everything under control. Just make sure that that ethereal form of that even freakier guy with the white hair and psychotic tendencies doesn't hack into his brain, and you'll be allright. <br>
<br>
11. If a guy kills your puppy, you can kill his entire family.<br>
<br>
12. a guy can twirl an 8-foot solid steel sword around his head with no problem, but he has no friggin' clue what to do with a pistol. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=prismrx>PrismRX</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/7/02 8:06:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=360.topic&index=55>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 12 things i've learned.</span><hr size=1> -Ever notice that there are no gas stations in Liberty City?<br>
-Ever notice the lack of bathrooms in Racoon city?<br>
-Ever notice that you can make a Fire Truck do a 360 degree flip and then fall backwards on a horde of police cars before self righting itself and driving away before catching on fire and exploding before the driver ends up at the hospital getting lectured by the gray infobox about health items?<br>
-Buses can fly.<br>
-You have to park a exploding garbage truck between two gas tanks to blow up a building instead of just shooting the gas tanks.<br>
-The bigger and more phallic a sword looks, the better it is.<br>
-Avoid people with prematurely white hair that hangs down to their knees.<br>
-Small green things in robes with knives are cheap.<br>
-The more wings a dragon has, the more insane it's attack is.<br>
-Aeris dies.  She's dead.  You can't get her back.  She's dead.  Face it.  She's dead.  She may have 2 lines on disk 2 but she's still dead and won't be coming back.  She's dead.<br>
<br>
-If you're fighting a giant evil corporation that manufactures biological weapons in secret, you will be obligated to:<br>
<br>
-Probably encounter small children who will make you want to shoot them.<br>
-Run away from some type of giant monster throughout the whole game.<br>
-Fly away from a giant explosion. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=reinvention>ReInvention</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/12/02 1:22:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=360.topic&index=56>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   lessons learned from GTA 3</span><hr size=1> -never shoot down a police helicopter, it will only encourage more to come along<br>
-when throwing molotovs, its best to stand a good distance away from where you throw them<br>
-(apparently harmless) old women with shopping bags are vicious and should not be approached <br>
-tramps are martial arts experts who are willing to fight to the death<br>
-its not wise to drive a car into the sea<br>
-don't trust dodgy geezers in puffa jackets who bowl around wearing earsets<br>
-the result of walking down the street carrying an Uzi is usually a bloodbath<br>
-fishmongers are probably just gangster rackets in disguise<br>
