-The police budget and replace hundreds of vehicles run over in your tank rampage.<br>
-When driving the tank, it care should be taken to lock the door, or cops will pull you out and arrest you.<br>
-Due to a military budget deficit, tanks are only used as road blocks and firing the main gun is strictly discouraged.<br>
-Prostitute+Convertable=instant hp.<br>
-Ironically, doing enough fire truck missions earns you a flame thrower.<br>
-When flying, ignore the floating island that has a bank, a road, and a few parked cars, it never existed.<br>
-It is not ironic when you see a police car chasing another police car.<br>
-Car bombs don't disappear. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=reinvention>ReInvention</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(12/12/02 2:04:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=360.topic&index=58>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: lessons learned from GTA 3</span><hr size=1> -contary to popular belief, radio stations are not beamed out live 24 hours a day, but are instead 40 minute excerts which are looped all day long<br>
-groups of 20 -30 people do not just walk up and down the same road for hours on end, appearing as if they enjoy this mundane life that they lead.<br>
-policeman are willing (and often do) take as many lives as possible on their quest to hunt you down over something minute such as overspeeding<br>
-ambulances do not deliver people to hospital who then get up and vacate the premises<br>
-Despite daily police spending reguarly reaching 6 figures, the force is still not willing to reduce cop numbers.<br>
